# Allowlist build context: exclude everything, then re-include only what
# the image needs. The runtime is app/ + apps/ plus the poetry manifests
# the Dockerfile COPYs; config comes from process env injected by compose
# (app/settings.py uses env_file=None), so env.env must never be baked
# into the image: CI bakes the tracked dev copy (with its GREFFER_ID)
# into the published greffon/greffer image, and in a configured dev
# checkout env.env carries a live GREFFER_TOKEN that a local build would
# otherwise ship. This also keeps tests/, cli/, .github, .git (local
# builds only; buildx git contexts strip it) and local artifacts
# (db.sqlite3, venv/, data/, rendered instance dirs) out of the context.
#
# Adding a new runtime file or directory? Re-include it with a ! line.
*
!app
!apps
!pyproject.toml
!poetry.lock
# Re-exclude junk inside the allowlisted dirs (last matching rule wins).
**/__pycache__
**/*.pyc
**/.DS_Store
